text: Corina Ssuschke-Voigt (born 9 May 1983) is a German national volleyball player. She played at the 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2009 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2010 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2011 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2011 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup, 2012 FIVB World Grand Prix, and 2013 FIVB World Grand Prix. She played for Lokomotiv Baku. == References == Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:German volleyball players
